title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Make a Wayang Plan that take the cities in interesting_municipalities_cities textfile and returns all organisations which have a matching municipality in the textfile. The textfile only have cities, but a municipality is usually called something like the city. Output the result in a textfile.

operations.udf: (t: (String, (String, org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record))) => { val rec = t._2._2; val orgName = rec.getField(3).toString; val mun = rec.getField(5).toString; s"${orgName} | ${mun}" }

log.thoughts: Read cities from the text file, normalize to lowercase, read organisations and normalize municipality, join on normalized municipality == city, format name|municipality and write to a text file.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped plan finalized for execution

data.table: (SELECT organisation_id, organisation_no, active_organisation, name, social_housing_org, municipality FROM organisation) as X

data.udf: (t: (String, (String, org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record))) => { val rec = t._2._2; val orgName = rec.getField(3).toString; val mun = rec.getField(5).toString; s"${orgName} | ${mun}" }

title: Wayang: Wayang plan sent to Wayang
Err: Wayang error. Plan executed unsucessful
